        <?php echo $this->stencil->setHeadline('GEOS'); ?>
        <p><strong>GEOS</strong> is a computer operating environment, graphical user interface, and suite of application software.</p>
        <p>Originally released as <strong>PC/GEOS</strong>, it runs on <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('DOS', 'OS'); ?> based, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('IBM PC compatible', 'PC'); ?> computers.</p>
        <p>The package later became <strong>GeoWorks Ensemble</strong>, then <strong>NewDeal Office</strong>, and is now <strong>Breadbox Ensemble</strong>.</p>
        <p>Versions for some handheld platforms were also released.</p>
        <p>PC/GEOS was first created by <strong>Berkeley Softworks</strong>, who later became <strong>GeoWorks Corporation</strong>. Version 4.0 was developed in 2001 by Breadbox Computer Company, LLC, and named Breadbox Ensemble.</p>
        <p>PC/GEOS should not be confused with the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('8-bit', 'IT'); ?> GEOS product from the same company, which runs on the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Commodore 64', 'ITH'); ?> and other computers using MOS <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('MOS 6502', 'CPU'); ?> compatible microprocessors.</p>
